"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149518","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2019-10-21","<p>We are considering the proposals from the Trustees of the Mineworkers’ Pension Scheme regarding protection for bonuses that have already accrued, and we will report back to the House in due course.</p>","Spelthorne","Kwasi  Kwarteng",,"2019-10-21T11:55:55.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149518/answer","Biography information for Kwasi  Kwarteng","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149518/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149518/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2019-10-15","Mineworkers' Pension Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment she has made of the potential effectiveness of the proposal of the trustees of the Mineworkers' Pension Scheme to guarantee beneficiaries' bonuses.","false","Biography information for Mary Creagh","Wakefield","Mary Creagh","629"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149519","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-10-21","<p>The Department is committed to supporting people with neurological and neurodevelopmental conditions, including Tourette’s syndrome, to live healthy and independent lives, and to tackle the stigma associated with such conditions. We have established a Neurodiversity Unit to consider what additional actions can be taken to support those with neurodevelopmental conditions to ensure that their needs are met.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2019-10-21T14:18:04.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149519/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149519/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149519/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-10-15","Tourette's Syndrome: Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what plans he is putting in place to (a) support people with Tourette’s syndrome and to (a) tackle the stigma associated with that condition.","false","Biography information for Ms Harriet Harman","Camberwell and Peckham","Ms Harriet Harman","406"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149520","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-10-21","<p>Advice for children and those at increased risk of having low vitamin D levels, can be found on both GOV.UK and from the National Health Service at the following links:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/phe-publishes-new-advice-on-vitamin-d" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/news/phe-publishes-new-advice-on-vitamin-d</a> <br></p><p><a href="https://www.nhs.uk/conditions/vitamins-and-minerals/vitamin-d/" target="_blank">https://www.nhs.uk/conditions/vitamins-and-minerals/vitamin-d/</a></p><p> </p><p>This advice is aimed at preventing vitamin D deficiency for the general population. Doctors may also investigate a patient’s vitamin or mineral status on an individual basis to correct deficiencies, which is a matter of clinical judgement.</p>","Bury St Edmunds","Jo Churchill",,"2019-10-21T16:52:28.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149520/answer","Biography information for Jo Churchill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149520/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149520/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-10-15","Vitamin D: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what steps the Government is taking to reduce vitamin D deficiency in children in primary and secondary schools in (a) the London borough of Southwark and (b) England.","false","Biography information for Ms Harriet Harman","Camberwell and Peckham","Ms Harriet Harman","407"
